{{Infobox scientist | name = Dieter Korn | image = | image_size = | birth_date = 1958 | birth_place = [[Sundern]] ([[Westphalia]]) | death_date = | death_place = | fields = [[Paleontology]] (paleomalocology) | nationality = [[Germany|German]] | work_institutions = [[Museum für Naturkunde]], [[Berlin]] | alma_mater = | known_for = [[Ammonite]] [[Evolution]] }} Dr. '''Dieter Korn''' (born 1958)<ref>Eugene V. Coan, Alan R. Kabat & Richard E. Petit (15 February) 2009. [http://www.malacological.org/publications/2400_malacology.html ''2,400 years of malacology, 6th ed.''] American Malacological Society. 830 pp. + 32 pp. (Annex of Collations).</ref> is a [[Germany|German]] scientist and [[paleontology|paleontologist]] specializing in research on [[ammonites]] and [[goniatites]].<ref name="korn">[http://www.museum.hu-berlin.de/mitarbeiter/mitarbeiter.asp?name=Dieter.Korn&lang=1 Web site] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090629224214/http://www.museum.hu-berlin.de/mitarbeiter/mitarbeiter.asp?name=Dieter.Korn&lang=1 |date=2009-06-29 }}</ref> He received his Ph.D. in 1996 from the [[University of Tübingen]] and is employed by the [[Museum für Naturkunde]] in [[Berlin, Germany]], in the Leibniz Institute for Research on Evolution and Biodiversity ([[Humboldt University]]). Dr Korn has published or coauthored over 100 papers since 1979,<ref name="CV">[http://www.museum.hu-berlin.de/mitarbeiter/publlist.asp?name=Dieter.Korn&id=8&lang=1 Curriculum vite] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090630063557/http://www.museum.hu-berlin.de/mitarbeiter/publlist.asp?name=Dieter.Korn&id=8&lang=1 |date=2009-06-30 }}</ref> including the description of numerous new species of cephalopods.
