{{Infobox scientist | name = Magnus Nordborg | native_name_lang = | image = | image_size = | alt = | caption = | birth_name = | birth_date = | birth_place = | death_date = | death_place = | resting_place = | resting_place_coordinates = | other_names = | residence = | citizenship = | nationality = | fields = {{Plainlist| * [[Population genetics]] }} | workplaces = {{Plainlist| * [[Lund University]] * [[University of Southern California]] * [[Gregor Mendel Institute]] }} | alma_mater = {{Plainlist| * [[Lund University]] (BSc) * [[Stanford University]] (PhD) }} | thesis_title = Deterministic models of natural selection | thesis_url = https://searchworks.stanford.edu/view/2942970 | thesis_year = 1994 | doctoral_advisor = [[Marcus Feldman]] | academic_advisors = | doctoral_students = | notable_students = | known_for = | influences = | influenced = | awards = | signature = | signature_alt = | website = | footnotes = | spouse = <!--(or | spouses = )--> | children = | death_cause = | education = | partner = <!--(or | partners = )--> | homepage = }}
'''Magnus Nordborg''' is a biologist specialising in [[population genetics]].<ref name="Kwon2017">{{cite web | last=Kwon | first=Diana | title=Scientists Offer Lab Space for Stranded Peers | website=The Scientist | date=2017-02-01 | url=https://www.the-scientist.com/?articles.view/articleNo/48281/title/Scientists-Offer-Lab-Space-for-Stranded-Peers/ | access-date=2018-02-17}}</ref> He is the scientific director of the [[Gregor Mendel Institute]] of the [[Austrian Academy of Sciences]], located at the [[Vienna Biocenter]].<ref name="GMIDirector">{{cite web | title=Management | website=Gregor Mendel Institute | url=https://www.gmi.oeaw.ac.at/about-us/management/ | access-date=2018-02-17}}</ref>
== Awards and honours == In 2003, Nordborg received the [[Sloan Research Fellowship]].<ref name="Sloan">{{cite web | title=Past Fellows | website=Sloan.org | url=https://sloan.org/past-fellows | access-date=2018-02-20}}</ref>
He was elected a fellow of the [[American Association for the Advancement of Science]] in 2010.<ref name="AAAS">{{cite web | title=AAAS Members Elected as Fellows | website=AAAS - The World's Largest General Scientific Society | date=2011-01-11 | url=https://www.aaas.org/news/2011/01/11/aaas-members-elected-fellows | access-date=2018-02-20}}</ref> In 2015, he was elected a member of the [[European Molecular Biology Organization]].<ref name="EMBO2015">{{cite web | last=User | first=Super | title=EMBO announces new members for 2015 | website=EMBO | date=2015-05-20 | url=http://www.embo.org/news/press-releases/2015/embo-announces-new-members-for-2015 | access-date=2018-02-20}}</ref>
Since 2013, he is a corresponding member of the [[Austrian Academy of Sciences]].<ref name="ÖAW">{{cite web | title=ÖAW Mitglieder Detail | website=Österreichische Akademie der Wissenschaften | url=https://www.oeaw.ac.at/m/nordborg-magnus/ | language=de | access-date=2018-02-20}}</ref>
