'''Riccardo Levi-Setti''' (July 11, 1927 – November 8, 2018<ref>{{cite web |url=https://news.uchicago.edu/story/riccardo-levi-setti-physicist-and-trilobite-collector-1927-2018 |title=Riccardo Levi-Setti, physicist and trilobite collector, 1927–2018 |author=<!--Not stated--> |date= |website=UChicago News |publisher=University of Chicago Office of Communications |access-date=November 21, 2018}}</ref>) was a [[Milan]]ese-born<ref name=magazine>{{cite news|url=http://magazine.uchicago.edu/0304/features/index-levi.html|title=Riccardo Levi-Setti — Trilobites|publisher=University of Chicago Magazine|accessdate=March 14, 2015}}</ref> [[emeritus]] professor of [[physics]] and [[paleontology]] at the [[University of Chicago]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://phys.org/news138540908.html|title=Exploding chromosomes fuel research about evolution of genetic storage|date=August 21, 2008|accessdate=March 14, 2015}}</ref> Prior to joining the University of Chicago in 1956, he worked at the [[Enrico Fermi Institute]], of which he became director in 1992.<ref name=enrico>{{cite news|url=http://neutrontrail.com/2011/06/enrico-fermi-time-capsule-opening/|title=Enrico Fermi Time Capsule Opening|date=June 2, 2011|accessdate=March 14, 2015}}</ref> In 2011 he, along with Roger Hildebrand, participated in the ceremony of the opening of the Enrico Fermi time capsule.<ref name=enrico/> 

In 1975 he wrote a book called ''Trilobites'', which was reissued in 1993.<ref name=magazine/> In 2014 his third book, called ''The Trilobite Book: A Visual Journey'', was published.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.timeshighereducation.co.uk/books/the-trilobite-book-a-visual-journey-by-riccardo-levi-setti/2015839.article|title=The Trilobite Book: A Visual Journey, by Riccardo Levi-Setti|work=[[Times Higher Education]]|date=September 25, 2014|accessdate=March 14, 2015}}</ref>

